titleInfo.title: United States of America v. $40,118.00 in United States Currency
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER granting 13 the parties' Stipulation; $5,000.00 of the defendant property shall be returned to the Claimant, Mark Medlock, by delivering the same to his attorney of record, James E. Schaefer. The Marshal shall deliver said amount by making payment to James E. Schaefer's Trust Account. Pursuant to this court's order dated August 29, 2005 6, the Marshal has published a notice of his intent to dispose of the property in such a manner as the Attorney General may direct. No person or entity has filed a Petition in response to said published notice, setting forth any legal or equitable interest in the subject property; The remaining defendant property, $35,118.00 in US Currency, is hereby forfeited to the United States, all right, title or interest in or to the defendant property held by any person or entity is hereby forever barred and foreclosed; the Marshal shall dispose of said $35,118.00 in US Currency in accordance with law; Upon Mr. Schaefer's receipt of the $5000.00 in US currency, as mentioned above, he shall file a receipt for said amount. Upon the filing of said receipt, this court shall enter a Judgment in this action. Signed by Judge Lyle E. Strom on 1/12/2006. 1 cert to USM and Copy to Financial. (MKR, )
